            "creation_date": 1490247689,
            "body": "<p>As per my understanding spring/jackson will not be able to recognise what type of object to create unless incoming json explicitly mentions about the same. See below link, it talks about abstract classes though. Basically there are multiple ways to achieve this, using jsonTypeinfo or argument resolvers etc. Check if this helps. <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7336920/abstract-classes-and-spring-mvc-modelattribute-requestparam\">Abstract classes and Spring MVC @ModelAttribute/@RequestParam<\/a><\/p>\n",
